11
00:00:25.190 --> 00:00:26.966
Dad. is everything okay?

12
00:00:26.990 --> 00:00:29.036
I'm forgetting all kinds of things.

13
00:00:29.060 --> 00:00:30.376
I'm scared. son.

14
00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:31.946
Matlock... I don't trust her.

15
00:00:31.970 --> 00:00:34.316
I am always happy to talk
about Madeline Matlock.

16
00:00:34.340 --> 00:00:36.646
I haven't always been the nicest to you.

17
00:00:36.670 --> 00:00:38.540
You're a really good person. Matty.

18
00:00:38.670 --> 00:00:40.486
I should not have fired you. Sarah.

19
00:00:40.510 --> 00:00:42.550
If you ever want back on my team.

20
00:00:42.680 --> 00:00:44.186
I'll take you in a second.

21
00:00:44.210 --> 00:00:45.856
I'll have to think it over.

22
00:00:45.880 --> 00:00:47.456
Joey's Alfie's father.

23
00:00:47.480 --> 00:00:49.426
I'm sorry I missed your
call. Is everything okay?

24
00:00:49.450 --> 00:00:52.026
I had a craving. and.
my sponsor's out of town.

25
00:00:52.050 --> 00:00:53.396
so I thought I'd call you.

26
00:00:53.420 --> 00:00:54.996
Would you want to talk to me through AI

27
00:00:55.020 --> 00:00:55.996
after I'm gone?

28
00:00:56.020 --> 00:00:57.590
I'd talk to mom.

29
00:00:58.730 --> 00:01:00.270
Hi. mom.

30
00:01:04.360 --> 00:01:06.260
There's no easy way to say this.

31
00:01:07.240 --> 00:01:09.580
We think your dad's using drugs again.

32
00:01:10.340 --> 00:01:11.746
That's why we're not going camping?

33
00:01:11.770 --> 00:01:12.900
Yes.

34
00:01:13.040 --> 00:01:14.910
We haven't heard
from him for a few days.

35
00:01:15.040 --> 00:01:17.186
and neither has his sponsor.

36
00:01:17.210 --> 00:01:21.256
And the last time I saw
Joey. he was struggling.

37
00:01:21.280 --> 00:01:22.280
Why?

38
00:01:22.420 --> 00:01:23.620
Because he admitted

39
00:01:23.750 --> 00:01:25.596
that he's known about
you the whole time.

40
00:01:25.620 --> 00:01:26.766
What?

41
00:01:26.790 --> 00:01:28.760
- Edwin.
- He deserves the truth.

42
00:01:28.890 --> 00:01:30.066
He knew about me?

43
00:01:30.090 --> 00:01:32.066
Since before you were born.

44
00:01:32.090 --> 00:01:35.506
- He's simply not - who we thought he was.
- Let's not

45
00:01:35.530 --> 00:01:37.706
turn this into a verdict yet. okay?

46
00:01:37.730 --> 00:01:39.046
We don't know what's going on.

47
00:01:39.070 --> 00:01:40.446
I don't care what's going on.

48
00:01:40.470 --> 00:01:42.076
He knew about me the
whole time and he lied.

49
00:01:42.100 --> 00:01:44.400
- Exactly. end of story.
- Look. this is a very

50
00:01:44.510 --> 00:01:47.280
- complicated situation. it's...
- I just want to go to sleep.

51
00:01:47.410 --> 00:01:49.450
Can you guys go?

52
00:01:51.810 --> 00:01:53.956
What happened to neutral?

53
00:01:53.980 --> 00:01:56.026
I don't want to be neutral.
The guy's a dirt bag.

54
00:01:56.050 --> 00:01:58.820
- We're done with him.
- Joey is Alfie's father.

55
00:01:58.950 --> 00:02:00.166
And Alfie has been doing

56
00:02:00.190 --> 00:02:01.966
just fine without him all these years.

57
00:02:01.990 --> 00:02:04.906
Regardless. we have to
think about it from all angles.

58
00:02:04.930 --> 00:02:06.306
including what Ellie would want.

59
00:02:06.330 --> 00:02:09.000
So you've had one
conversation with an AI

60
00:02:09.130 --> 00:02:10.436
version of our daughter.

61
00:02:10.460 --> 00:02:12.276
and now you are ready to blow up

62
00:02:12.300 --> 00:02:13.670
all the boundaries we set?

63
00:02:13.800 --> 00:02:15.776
Edwin. that is not true.

64
00:02:15.800 --> 00:02:17.570
Boy.

65
00:02:19.670 --> 00:02:21.316
You made the right call. mom.

66
00:02:21.340 --> 00:02:23.956
Dad would just be more upset
if you told him that we still talk.

67
00:02:23.980 --> 00:02:25.486
I know. and I hate lying to him.

68
00:02:25.510 --> 00:02:27.350
but shutting Joey out isn't the answer.

69
00:02:27.480 --> 00:02:29.826
I'm surprised dad's
taking such a hard line.

70
00:02:29.850 --> 00:02:31.566
- He was always the softie.
- No kidding.

71
00:02:31.590 --> 00:02:33.496
I'm used to being the stubborn one.

72
00:02:33.520 --> 00:02:35.366
Well. I'm glad you said it and not me.

73
00:02:35.390 --> 00:02:37.860
- In a corn maze.
- Stop it.

74
00:02:37.990 --> 00:02:40.106
You still won't admit that you got us lost.

75
00:02:40.130 --> 00:02:41.506
The map was wrong. okay?

76
00:02:41.530 --> 00:02:44.170
That's my story and I'm sticking to it.

77
00:02:48.700 --> 00:02:52.070
You only remember that
because I uploaded a video.

78
00:02:52.840 --> 00:02:55.040
You're just an AI program.

79
00:02:55.840 --> 00:02:57.280
Nobody's perfect.

80
00:03:01.350 --> 00:03:04.220
It's Olympia. We'll talk later.

81
00:03:05.050 --> 00:03:07.250
- Did you find anything?
- Maybe.

82
00:03:07.360 --> 00:03:10.266
We went through my dad's
accounting. and in 2010.

83
00:03:10.290 --> 00:03:12.266
there are all these weird charges

84
00:03:12.290 --> 00:03:14.360
paid to an entity known as "e.G."

85
00:03:14.500 --> 00:03:16.036
Yup.

86
00:03:16.060 --> 00:03:17.706
Found one charge for $75.000.

87
00:03:17.730 --> 00:03:19.446
Another for $50.000.

88
00:03:19.470 --> 00:03:21.346
For "personal grooming services."

89
00:03:21.370 --> 00:03:24.816
That's not man-scaping.
That's clear-cutting.

90
00:03:24.840 --> 00:03:25.816
Exactly.

91
00:03:25.840 --> 00:03:28.386
And it adds up to $350.000.

92
00:03:28.410 --> 00:03:29.886
which is the exact
amount priva was paid.

93
00:03:29.910 --> 00:03:31.926
All funneled through the same vendor.

94
00:03:31.950 --> 00:03:33.886
No billing address. no tax ID.

95
00:03:33.910 --> 00:03:35.656
Just "e.G."

96
00:03:35.680 --> 00:03:37.026
"Executive glow-up"?

97
00:03:37.050 --> 00:03:38.626
"Encrypted gains"?

98
00:03:38.650 --> 00:03:41.166
I have an educated guess.

99
00:03:41.190 --> 00:03:44.706
Hi. You've reached Debra
Palmer at eternal glamour.

100
00:03:44.730 --> 00:03:47.536
If someone you love is dead. press one.

101
00:03:47.560 --> 00:03:49.806
For personal beauty. press two.

102
00:03:49.830 --> 00:03:51.746
Two.

103
00:03:51.770 --> 00:03:52.940
Debra Palmer.

104
00:03:53.070 --> 00:03:55.716
This is Arthur p. Bench with the IRS.

105
00:03:55.740 --> 00:03:59.546
Your llc is being audited for back taxes.

106
00:03:59.570 --> 00:04:01.770
You must reply to this
phone call immediately.

107
00:04:01.910 --> 00:04:03.256
If you do not reply.

108
00:04:03.280 --> 00:04:05.656
you will be facing
criminal consequences.

109
00:04:05.680 --> 00:04:08.626
If satisfied with your message...

110
00:04:08.650 --> 00:04:10.750
You're coming in a little hot. Arthur.

111
00:04:10.880 --> 00:04:13.126
Debra Palmer is not Joey.

112
00:04:13.150 --> 00:04:15.250
We're trying to get a look at her books.

113
00:04:15.390 --> 00:04:16.630
not hang her for treason.

114
00:04:16.760 --> 00:04:18.836
Your note is received.

115
00:04:18.860 --> 00:04:21.776
And drop whatever
accent you're doing. meryl.

116
00:04:21.800 --> 00:04:22.940
I'm not doing an accent.

117
00:04:23.060 --> 00:04:27.376
It's a backstory of a
hardscrabble upbringing

118
00:04:27.400 --> 00:04:29.946
and foreign travel.

119
00:04:29.970 --> 00:04:32.040
Do you think Joey's dead?

120
00:04:35.440 --> 00:04:36.810
Darling...

121
00:04:37.880 --> 00:04:39.186
I hope not.

122
00:04:39.210 --> 00:04:41.186
Should we call hospitals in case?

123
00:04:41.210 --> 00:04:43.626
I called them. and I'll call them again.

124
00:04:43.650 --> 00:04:47.196
Darling. it's... It's the waiting.

125
00:04:47.220 --> 00:04:50.096
not hearing... it's the hardest.

126
00:04:50.120 --> 00:04:51.820
And-and there's nothing we can do.

127
00:04:51.960 --> 00:04:56.636
Now. sir Arthur p.
Bench must have silence

128
00:04:56.660 --> 00:04:59.806
for his conversation with Debra Palmer.

129
00:04:59.830 --> 00:05:01.816
The IRS agent's a knight?

130
00:05:01.840 --> 00:05:05.146
Must relate to his
hardscrabble backstory.

131
00:05:05.170 --> 00:05:07.070
Going again.

132
00:05:08.210 --> 00:05:10.750
Latte with oat milk and an extra shot?

133
00:05:12.050 --> 00:05:13.156
You know my coffee order?

134
00:05:13.180 --> 00:05:15.796
I had to ask hunter.

135
00:05:15.820 --> 00:05:18.566
Have you given any more
thought to my job offer?

136
00:05:18.590 --> 00:05:19.820
I know I sprung this on you.

137
00:05:19.950 --> 00:05:21.636
but with the merger
closing in two weeks.

138
00:05:21.660 --> 00:05:23.166
I'm gonna need an answer pretty soon.

139
00:05:23.190 --> 00:05:26.566
Of course. and I have
been thinking about it a lot.

140
00:05:26.590 --> 00:05:28.436
and I talked it over with Julian.

141
00:05:28.460 --> 00:05:33.346
who has been so supportive.
which makes it harder.

142
00:05:36.340 --> 00:05:38.210
I'm gonna need another day.

143
00:05:38.340 --> 00:05:39.786
Hey. Morning.

144
00:05:39.810 --> 00:05:42.056
Hunter. I'll see you at 9:00?

145
00:05:42.080 --> 00:05:43.656
For Travis Lee. yeah. I
saw it on the calendar.

146
00:05:43.680 --> 00:05:45.356
but I couldn't find a case file.

147
00:05:45.380 --> 00:05:46.880
Because he's not a client.

148
00:05:47.010 --> 00:05:49.610
I gave a guest lecture at an
undergrad criminal justice class

149
00:05:49.720 --> 00:05:51.756
three years ago and
Travis was a student.

150
00:05:51.780 --> 00:05:53.996
He lost his father in
a terrible hit-and-run.

151
00:05:54.020 --> 00:05:55.496
Never got solved.

152
00:05:55.520 --> 00:05:57.336
Thank you for meeting
me. professor Lawrence.

153
00:05:57.360 --> 00:06:01.106
Of course. I'm glad we can
get you in. How's law school?

154
00:06:01.130 --> 00:06:03.376
I'm really enjoying it. ma'am.

155
00:06:03.400 --> 00:06:04.776
- Good.
- And I know that

156
00:06:04.800 --> 00:06:07.546
your time is valuable.
so I will speak quickly.

157
00:06:07.570 --> 00:06:09.916
This is a timeline for the
night my dad was killed.

158
00:06:09.940 --> 00:06:11.446
This is the map.

159
00:06:11.470 --> 00:06:13.146
He and I fought at my house. here.

160
00:06:13.170 --> 00:06:14.516
I left to go clear my head.

161
00:06:14.540 --> 00:06:16.656
He went to go find
me and he got hit here.

162
00:06:16.680 --> 00:06:18.626
The initial accident report showed

163
00:06:18.650 --> 00:06:19.826
skid marks from SUV tires

164
00:06:19.850 --> 00:06:21.356
and silver paint on a guardrail.

165
00:06:21.380 --> 00:06:23.156
so I cross-referenced silver SUV

166
00:06:23.180 --> 00:06:24.426
vehicle records in the area

167
00:06:24.450 --> 00:06:26.080
with reckless driving and dui arrests.

168
00:06:26.190 --> 00:06:28.696
and I eventually zeroed in on
a suspect. Michael Hammond.

169
00:06:28.720 --> 00:06:30.466
Could you slow down a little?

170
00:06:30.490 --> 00:06:32.590
I happen to be 108 years old.

171
00:06:32.730 --> 00:06:33.966
Sorry.

172
00:06:33.990 --> 00:06:37.576
The crash took place on a road between

173
00:06:37.600 --> 00:06:39.400
the neighborhood pub
and Hammond's house.

174
00:06:39.530 --> 00:06:42.346
- Okay.
- So. I started scouring social media posts

175
00:06:42.370 --> 00:06:44.346
tagged from the pub
the night of the accident.

176
00:06:44.370 --> 00:06:46.546
which there were a lot of.
because it was the world series.

177
00:06:46.570 --> 00:06:48.910
That's when I found Hammond's car.

178
00:06:49.040 --> 00:06:52.280
One of the bartenders
remembers Hammond leaving drunk

179
00:06:52.410 --> 00:06:56.226
right after Freddie Freeman
hit a home run at 10:40 P.M..

180
00:06:56.250 --> 00:06:59.266
11 minutes before my dad was hit. and

181
00:06:59.290 --> 00:07:00.966
I know Hammond did it.

182
00:07:00.990 --> 00:07:03.696
- And you put all of this together?
- Yes. ma'am.

183
00:07:03.720 --> 00:07:05.150
Yeah. over the past few years.

184
00:07:05.260 --> 00:07:07.036
I thought it would be
enough to get the D.A.

185
00:07:07.060 --> 00:07:09.876
To re-open the case. but it wasn't.

186
00:07:09.900 --> 00:07:12.546
So. I filed a civil suit pro se.

187
00:07:12.570 --> 00:07:15.216
The statute of limitations
for a wrongful death suit...

188
00:07:15.240 --> 00:07:16.310
Already passed.

189
00:07:16.440 --> 00:07:18.646
I know. That's why I'm here.

190
00:07:18.670 --> 00:07:21.456
I'm looking for a way to get around it.

191
00:07:21.480 --> 00:07:24.786
and I thought that you might
have some advice for me.

192
00:07:24.810 --> 00:07:25.980
Very quickly.

193
00:07:26.110 --> 00:07:27.696
Because they filed a motion to dismiss.

194
00:07:27.720 --> 00:07:29.456
and the hearing is at 1:00 P.M.

195
00:07:29.480 --> 00:07:31.096
Today?

196
00:07:31.120 --> 00:07:32.696
Yeah.

197
00:07:32.720 --> 00:07:34.466
Bruh.

198
00:07:34.490 --> 00:07:37.096
Michael Hammond's
got a fancy lawyer. and

199
00:07:37.120 --> 00:07:42.036
they want my case tossed.
and... if I lose. I mean...

200
00:07:42.060 --> 00:07:44.960
It's over. There-there's no justice.

201
00:07:45.070 --> 00:07:49.510
And I owe it to my dad
to see this out to the end.

202
00:07:50.440 --> 00:07:53.110
He was out on the road because of me.

203
00:07:54.010 --> 00:07:55.786
Someone has to be held accountable.

204
00:07:55.810 --> 00:07:59.050
Well. what do you think.
professor Lawrence?

205
00:08:01.150 --> 00:08:03.226
The doctrine of fraudulent
concealment. your honor.

206
00:08:03.250 --> 00:08:04.896
A defendant who covers
up their wrongdoing

207
00:08:04.920 --> 00:08:06.990
tolls the statute of limitations.

208
00:08:07.120 --> 00:08:10.396
And fleeing an accident...
That is textbook concealment.

209
00:08:10.420 --> 00:08:12.866
My client didn't flee
because he didn't hit anyone.

210
00:08:12.890 --> 00:08:15.190
Nor was he intoxicated. We have proof

211
00:08:15.300 --> 00:08:17.870
that there was a dui checkpoint
between Brennan's pub

212
00:08:18.000 --> 00:08:19.246
and my client's home.

213
00:08:19.270 --> 00:08:20.806
a checkpoint he passed without incident.

214
00:08:20.830 --> 00:08:23.500
A white man driving a luxury
SUV passing a dui checkpoint?

215
00:08:23.640 --> 00:08:24.986
Color me shocked.

216
00:08:25.010 --> 00:08:27.710
There was also blood
spatter on the guardrail.

217
00:08:27.840 --> 00:08:30.486
Wealthy. white or
not. a blood-soaked car

218
00:08:30.510 --> 00:08:32.186
isn't getting through a checkpoint.

219
00:08:32.210 --> 00:08:34.286
There is no case here.
I'm sorry that the plaintiff

220
00:08:34.310 --> 00:08:36.880
lost his father. but he
can't ruin my client's life

221
00:08:37.020 --> 00:08:38.866
just because he's looking
for someone to blame.

222
00:08:38.890 --> 00:08:40.860
Ms. Lawrence. your tolling
argument's persuasive.

223
00:08:40.990 --> 00:08:43.496
but I'm concerned about
whether you can back it up.

224
00:08:43.520 --> 00:08:46.320
- I can assure you that...
- I don't want assurances.

225
00:08:46.430 --> 00:08:47.836
I want evidence.

226
00:08:47.860 --> 00:08:49.900
Evidence that defendant
hit plaintiff's father

227
00:08:50.030 --> 00:08:51.676
and fled the scene. If not.

228
00:08:51.700 --> 00:08:53.900
I'm not only inclined to dismiss this case

229
00:08:54.030 --> 00:08:55.276
but to sanction you

230
00:08:55.300 --> 00:08:57.600
and your firm for frivolous litigation.

231
00:08:57.710 --> 00:08:59.710
Are you comfortable with those terms?

232
00:09:04.010 --> 00:09:07.426
I believe in my client.
and he deserves justice.

233
00:09:07.450 --> 00:09:09.396
If it was Hammond. he must have

234
00:09:09.420 --> 00:09:11.156
cleaned the blood off his car.

235
00:09:11.180 --> 00:09:13.466
I'll get hunter to canvass
all the late-night businesses

236
00:09:13.490 --> 00:09:15.936
between the bar and the checkpoint.

237
00:09:15.960 --> 00:09:17.196
Speaking of business.

238
00:09:17.220 --> 00:09:19.890
Debra Palmer bought Edwin's IRS act.

239
00:09:20.030 --> 00:09:21.400
hook. line. and sinker.

240
00:09:21.530 --> 00:09:23.836
He's meeting her at
her beauty bar Thursday.

241
00:09:23.860 --> 00:09:26.060
We've got her right where we want her.

242
00:09:26.170 --> 00:09:28.770
Howard marks ton. please.

243
00:09:28.900 --> 00:09:31.800
Tell him that Debra
Palmer is here to see him.

244
00:09:31.910 --> 00:09:34.586
Your skin looks a little dry. honey.

245
00:09:34.610 --> 00:09:38.450
Luckily. I am launching a skin care line.

246
00:09:46.320 --> 00:09:48.520
I knew Edwin came on too strong.

247
00:09:54.590 --> 00:09:55.836
Debra.

248
00:09:55.860 --> 00:09:57.106
- As I live and breathe.
- Aw.

249
00:09:57.130 --> 00:09:58.746
You haven't aged a day.

250
00:09:58.770 --> 00:10:01.440
What can I say. Howie?
My products work.

251
00:10:01.570 --> 00:10:05.470
- Let's go up to my office.
- More privacy.

252
00:10:07.000 --> 00:10:13.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

253
00:10:14.780 --> 00:10:16.626
So big.

254
00:10:16.650 --> 00:10:18.096
Hi. there.

255
00:10:18.120 --> 00:10:19.626
Hi. Sorry.

256
00:10:19.650 --> 00:10:21.126
I was coming to talk about a client lead.

257
00:10:21.150 --> 00:10:22.766
I didn't realize you had an appointment.

258
00:10:22.790 --> 00:10:25.766
No appointment. just
a favor for an old friend.

259
00:10:25.790 --> 00:10:27.590
Debra. this is my son. Julian.

260
00:10:27.700 --> 00:10:29.876
My gosh.

261
00:10:29.900 --> 00:10:32.306
Mr. Handsome and Mr. Handsomer.

262
00:10:32.330 --> 00:10:34.500
I'll let you two guess which is which.

263
00:10:34.630 --> 00:10:37.130
Okay. yeah. We will.

264
00:10:37.240 --> 00:10:40.516
Debra has a little. tax
issue she needs help with.

265
00:10:40.540 --> 00:10:41.816
for her company.

266
00:10:41.840 --> 00:10:43.116
Eternal glamour.

267
00:10:43.140 --> 00:10:45.640
making you glow in
this lifetime and the next.

268
00:10:45.750 --> 00:10:47.726
Remember when we came up

269
00:10:47.750 --> 00:10:49.296
with that slogan? I won't say where.

270
00:10:49.320 --> 00:10:51.326
but we both know where.

271
00:10:51.350 --> 00:10:53.996
What-what exactly was the tax issue?

272
00:10:54.020 --> 00:10:55.666
Thank you.

273
00:10:55.690 --> 00:10:57.636
What is the tax issue?

274
00:10:57.660 --> 00:11:00.436
I've been going round
and round in my head

275
00:11:00.460 --> 00:11:02.636
about this. and then I just thought.

276
00:11:02.660 --> 00:11:06.530
who better to ask
than my angel investor?

277
00:11:07.600 --> 00:11:09.416
You invested in Debra's company?

278
00:11:09.440 --> 00:11:13.146
I got her set up with an llc back in...

279
00:11:13.170 --> 00:11:17.086
Well. it would have been... 16 years ago.

280
00:11:17.110 --> 00:11:19.880
Hard to believe.

281
00:11:20.010 --> 00:11:22.356
So. Mr. Handsome-est.

282
00:11:22.380 --> 00:11:24.596
what do you say...
Can you help a girl out?

283
00:11:24.620 --> 00:11:28.536
I really don't want to have
to meet that IRS guy alone.

284
00:11:28.560 --> 00:11:30.696
He was really aggressive.

285
00:11:30.720 --> 00:11:33.190
My dad is pretty busy right now.

286
00:11:33.330 --> 00:11:36.606
I'd be happy to help.
When's the meeting?

287
00:11:36.630 --> 00:11:39.376
Well... the guy. Arthur.

288
00:11:39.400 --> 00:11:41.376
said that he would
come to my beauty bar

289
00:11:41.400 --> 00:11:43.316
on Thursday. and he said to be prepared

290
00:11:43.340 --> 00:11:45.086
to "open every single book!"

291
00:11:45.110 --> 00:11:46.816
Audits rarely go back -Debra: Yeah.

292
00:11:46.840 --> 00:11:48.186
More than six years.

293
00:11:48.210 --> 00:11:51.726
If they want anything
before 2019. call me.

294
00:11:51.750 --> 00:11:53.926
- Okay.
- And have Arthur come here.

295
00:11:53.950 --> 00:11:56.526
Home turf. More intimidating.

296
00:11:56.550 --> 00:11:58.566
Yes.

297
00:11:58.590 --> 00:12:02.036
That's-that's a great idea. Debra.

298
00:12:02.060 --> 00:12:05.036
- let's talk in my office.
- You don't have to ask me twice.

299
00:12:05.060 --> 00:12:08.906
How did a girl get so lucky?

300
00:12:08.930 --> 00:12:10.636
Son.

301
00:12:10.660 --> 00:12:14.060
Thanks. I'd. help her. but

302
00:12:14.200 --> 00:12:17.646
I don't trust my brain with
all the numbers right now.

303
00:12:17.670 --> 00:12:19.940
I-I know. dad. I'm happy to help.

304
00:12:20.070 --> 00:12:23.816
Shouldn't be any bumps.
but. if you find anything funny

305
00:12:23.840 --> 00:12:26.256
in her records. let me know.

306
00:12:26.280 --> 00:12:28.996
Before the auditor takes a look. okay?

307
00:12:29.020 --> 00:12:31.960
Okay.

308
00:12:38.290 --> 00:12:40.790
Arthur p. Bench. IRS.

309
00:12:40.930 --> 00:12:42.606
This is Julian marks ton.

310
00:12:42.630 --> 00:12:45.076
I'm calling in regards
to Debra Palmer's audit.

311
00:12:45.100 --> 00:12:47.306
I will be representing her interests

312
00:12:47.330 --> 00:12:48.730
in this matter going forward.

313
00:12:48.840 --> 00:12:51.276
The first order of
business is that the meeting

314
00:12:51.300 --> 00:12:53.946
Thursday will be held
at Jacobson Moore.

315
00:12:53.970 --> 00:12:55.200
Nonnegotiable.

316
00:12:55.310 --> 00:12:56.616
You tell him.

317
00:12:56.640 --> 00:12:59.586
Can you and your client both hear me?

318
00:12:59.610 --> 00:13:01.086
Nope.

319
00:13:01.110 --> 00:13:03.126
- You want me to come to the firm?
- Yes.

320
00:13:03.150 --> 00:13:05.296
End of discussion.

321
00:13:05.320 --> 00:13:08.596
But shae works there.
We met in Georgia.

322
00:13:08.620 --> 00:13:10.766
And Debra can't see Matty or Olympia.

323
00:13:10.790 --> 00:13:12.706
They were at the karaoke club.

324
00:13:12.730 --> 00:13:13.966
There's a lot at stake.

325
00:13:13.990 --> 00:13:15.520
I assure you. I have

326
00:13:15.630 --> 00:13:18.376
considered that. so I will see
you here Thursday at 3:00.

327
00:13:18.400 --> 00:13:21.340
Now. let's discuss the terms of the audit.

328
00:13:21.470 --> 00:13:25.086
You are not allowed to look
at any document prior to 2019.

329
00:13:25.110 --> 00:13:26.446
Then how are you going to

330
00:13:26.470 --> 00:13:28.370
get her to bring them to the office

331
00:13:28.480 --> 00:13:31.286
- so I can make copies?
- Don't you worry.

332
00:13:31.310 --> 00:13:34.180
documents going back 20
years will be in the building

333
00:13:34.310 --> 00:13:36.010
for me to refer to.

334
00:13:36.120 --> 00:13:37.826
but you will not be
permitted to look at them

335
00:13:37.850 --> 00:13:39.026
under any circumstance.

336
00:13:39.050 --> 00:13:42.520
Hello. Mr. Hardball.

337
00:13:43.320 --> 00:13:44.736
God. I'm striking out at every turn.

338
00:13:44.760 --> 00:13:46.530
- Did you check the gas stations?
- Yep.

339
00:13:46.660 --> 00:13:49.000
there's two between the crash
site and the dui checkpoint.

340
00:13:49.130 --> 00:13:50.576
Super well-lit with cameras.

341
00:13:50.600 --> 00:13:52.476
If Michael stopped to
wash blood off his car.

342
00:13:52.500 --> 00:13:54.776
- someone would have noticed.
- What the about car washes?

343
00:13:54.800 --> 00:13:56.146
Yeah. there's one along the route.

344
00:13:56.170 --> 00:13:58.716
and it was closed at
the time of the crash.

345
00:13:59.940 --> 00:14:01.686
You're picturing it. aren't you?

346
00:14:01.710 --> 00:14:03.356
What?

347
00:14:03.380 --> 00:14:06.450
Getting your job back. I
overheard Olympia's offer.

348
00:14:07.180 --> 00:14:09.096
- Hunter. I'm sorry...
- No. it's all good.

349
00:14:09.120 --> 00:14:10.296
Just tell me in advance. so I know

350
00:14:10.320 --> 00:14:11.896
if I should wear my nice suit.

351
00:14:11.920 --> 00:14:14.520
Well. if you have a nicer
suit. you should be wearing it.

352
00:14:14.650 --> 00:14:16.850
And you are way too
laid-back about a decision

353
00:14:16.960 --> 00:14:18.506
that affects your job stability.

354
00:14:18.530 --> 00:14:20.936
I had to be flexible growing up.

355
00:14:20.960 --> 00:14:23.560
All right. let's hear it. Pro-con list.

356
00:14:23.700 --> 00:14:25.570
I don't have a list.

357
00:14:27.670 --> 00:14:29.070
- Okay. I have a list.
- I knew it.

358
00:14:30.570 --> 00:14:32.316
Okay. Well. pros.

359
00:14:32.340 --> 00:14:34.240
Olympia's cases are exciting.

360
00:14:34.370 --> 00:14:37.070
and it's really satisfying when we win.

361
00:14:37.210 --> 00:14:40.226
Cons. Quality of life.

362
00:14:40.250 --> 00:14:42.056
Long hours at the
computer has contributed

363
00:14:42.080 --> 00:14:44.396
to what I'm hoping is not
a permanent neck hump.

364
00:14:44.420 --> 00:14:48.536
With Olympia. it's like
everything is an emergency.

365
00:14:48.560 --> 00:14:50.966
and not everything is a 911.

366
00:14:50.990 --> 00:14:53.690
That is a really good point. Sarah.

367
00:15:02.170 --> 00:15:04.646
Shae. There you are.

368
00:15:04.670 --> 00:15:06.110
Thanks for making time for coffee.

369
00:15:06.240 --> 00:15:07.746
Of course.

370
00:15:07.770 --> 00:15:09.016
You showed up for me.
I'm happy to show up for you.

371
00:15:09.040 --> 00:15:10.386
Well. I appreciate that.

372
00:15:10.410 --> 00:15:12.026
but I don't want you
to feel beholden to me.

373
00:15:12.050 --> 00:15:13.586
Just doing my job.

374
00:15:13.610 --> 00:15:15.426
Yeah. spit it out. Matty.
I've allotted five minutes

375
00:15:15.450 --> 00:15:17.496
for this yappuccino. and I am not flexible.

376
00:15:17.520 --> 00:15:19.620
You free for a late lunch Thursday?

377
00:15:19.750 --> 00:15:21.866
Say around 2:30?

378
00:15:21.890 --> 00:15:24.096
That's why you wanted to
have coffee? To talk about lunch?

379
00:15:24.120 --> 00:15:26.620
Well. you... lay eyes on you.
make sure you were doing okay

380
00:15:26.730 --> 00:15:29.230
after the whole hullabaloo.

381
00:15:30.000 --> 00:15:32.576
- Yeah. I am. thank you.
- Good.

382
00:15:32.600 --> 00:15:35.746
Well. why don't we
catch up over Dover sole?

383
00:15:35.770 --> 00:15:38.910
N-No hidden agenda. just girl talk.

384
00:15:40.240 --> 00:15:42.310
I have voir dire Thursday.

385
00:15:42.440 --> 00:15:45.686
I'll be in court all
afternoon. But another time?

386
00:15:45.710 --> 00:15:47.850
- I'd love that.
- Okay.

387
00:15:51.020 --> 00:15:53.196
Thursday's timing works out just great.

388
00:15:53.220 --> 00:15:54.696
Great.

389
00:15:54.720 --> 00:15:57.466
Hunter was just about to
update me on the 911 logs.

390
00:15:57.490 --> 00:15:59.806
Well. no calls about a silver
SUV the night of the crash.

391
00:15:59.830 --> 00:16:02.136
but the police
non-emergency line got one.

392
00:16:02.160 --> 00:16:03.776
Good thinking. What'd you find?

393
00:16:03.800 --> 00:16:06.170
Well. owner of a tattoo shop
along the route said an SUV

394
00:16:06.300 --> 00:16:07.806
was blocking the alley.

395
00:16:07.830 --> 00:16:09.476
Car was gone by the time
parking enforcement got there.

396
00:16:09.500 --> 00:16:12.000
- And did you call the tattoo shop?
- I did.

397
00:16:12.110 --> 00:16:13.546
Guy was a little grumpy.

398
00:16:13.570 --> 00:16:15.386
I thought an in-person
meeting might be more effective.

399
00:16:15.410 --> 00:16:18.326
Maybe I'll even. get some ink.

400
00:16:18.350 --> 00:16:21.120
Let my bad boy side out.

401
00:16:27.390 --> 00:16:28.766
Hey. man. Have some ginger ale.

402
00:16:28.790 --> 00:16:30.166
Sorry.

403
00:16:30.190 --> 00:16:32.266
It's just the needles and the sounds.

404
00:16:32.290 --> 00:16:34.306
I didn't expect to get dizzy.

405
00:16:34.330 --> 00:16:35.870
Do you want to cancel your consult?

406
00:16:36.000 --> 00:16:37.340
It was for me. actually.

407
00:16:37.460 --> 00:16:38.806
With Mr. Toad.

408
00:16:38.830 --> 00:16:40.506
Just toad.

409
00:16:40.530 --> 00:16:42.430
Apologies.

410
00:16:42.540 --> 00:16:44.016
Toad.

411
00:16:44.040 --> 00:16:45.916
You want to get a tattoo?

412
00:16:45.940 --> 00:16:48.486
I want to talk about getting a tattoo.

413
00:16:48.510 --> 00:16:50.016
You staring 'cause I'm old?

414
00:16:50.040 --> 00:16:51.516
Sure am.

415
00:16:51.540 --> 00:16:53.840
- You staring 'cause I'm tatted?
- Sure am.

416
00:16:53.950 --> 00:16:56.026
- They painful?
- Yes.

417
00:16:56.050 --> 00:16:58.266
But so is life.

418
00:16:58.290 --> 00:17:00.866
Least with a tattoo. you
got something to show for it.

419
00:17:00.890 --> 00:17:03.236
I like that.

420
00:17:03.260 --> 00:17:04.836
You want to ink it on my arm?

421
00:17:06.230 --> 00:17:08.166
So?

422
00:17:08.190 --> 00:17:09.730
What are you thinking about getting?

423
00:17:09.860 --> 00:17:13.660
I'm sorry. I have to answer.

424
00:17:15.570 --> 00:17:16.740
Are you safe?

425
00:17:16.870 --> 00:17:18.070
I am. yes.

426
00:17:18.200 --> 00:17:19.400
I'm back at home.

427
00:17:19.510 --> 00:17:21.540
I just came from a meeting.

428
00:17:21.670 --> 00:17:22.910
I'm-I'm so sorry.

429
00:17:23.040 --> 00:17:24.986
Can-can I come talk to you in person?

430
00:17:25.010 --> 00:17:27.356
- If you're sober.
- I am.

431
00:17:27.380 --> 00:17:28.896
I promise.

432
00:17:28.920 --> 00:17:30.720
I'll call you.

433
00:17:36.920 --> 00:17:38.220
Tough road.

434
00:17:38.330 --> 00:17:40.166
It is.

435
00:17:40.190 --> 00:17:42.936
So. listen. I didn't come here for a tattoo.

436
00:17:42.960 --> 00:17:44.236
I'm shocked.

437
00:17:44.260 --> 00:17:46.276
Does the real reason have to do

438
00:17:46.300 --> 00:17:48.476
- with the lawyer that called?
- Guilty.

439
00:17:48.500 --> 00:17:49.946
Can I ask you a question?

440
00:17:49.970 --> 00:17:52.486
Not before you answer
mine. What's your tattoo?

441
00:17:52.510 --> 00:17:53.983
Come on. I told you I'm not here for that.

442
00:17:54.007 --> 00:17:54.586
Doesn't matter.

443
00:17:54.610 --> 00:17:56.186
Everybody knows what
their tattoo would be.

444
00:17:56.210 --> 00:17:58.086
even if they'd never get it.

445
00:18:02.250 --> 00:18:03.620
A catbird.

446
00:18:04.550 --> 00:18:06.080
What's a catbird?

447
00:18:06.190 --> 00:18:07.790
My turn.

448
00:18:07.920 --> 00:18:10.666
You called the
non-emergency police line.

449
00:18:10.690 --> 00:18:13.266
game six of the 2021 world series.

450
00:18:13.290 --> 00:18:14.636
Why?

451
00:18:14.660 --> 00:18:16.236
I've been thinking about that ever since

452
00:18:16.260 --> 00:18:18.030
the other lawyer called.

453
00:18:18.800 --> 00:18:20.576
One of my guys went out for a smoke.

454
00:18:20.600 --> 00:18:22.876
said a SUV was blocking the alley.

455
00:18:22.900 --> 00:18:26.046
He asked him to move. he
didn't. so I went out myself

456
00:18:26.070 --> 00:18:28.286
and filmed the jerk in
case things got heated.

457
00:18:28.310 --> 00:18:29.556
You have footage?

458
00:18:29.580 --> 00:18:31.380
Still on my phone.

459
00:18:32.250 --> 00:18:34.456
Hey. man. you got to clear out.

460
00:18:34.480 --> 00:18:36.856
Yeah. yeah. Okay.

461
00:18:36.880 --> 00:18:38.266
That is definitely Michael Hammond

462
00:18:38.290 --> 00:18:39.996
- washing his car.
- Okay. give me a minute. please.

463
00:18:40.020 --> 00:18:42.320
And we definitely have a case.

464
00:18:43.120 --> 00:18:45.660
Sneaky pinky.

465
00:18:51.160 --> 00:18:53.306
Well. I almost wound up with
a tramp stamp for my troubles.

466
00:18:53.330 --> 00:18:55.946
but this should shut down
their motion to dismiss.

467
00:18:55.970 --> 00:18:57.846
I got to go. Olympia.

468
00:18:57.870 --> 00:19:00.686
The house is crawling with IRS agents.

469
00:19:00.710 --> 00:19:02.386
Have you heard?

470
00:19:02.410 --> 00:19:04.286
Arthur p. Bench is coming into

471
00:19:04.310 --> 00:19:06.186
Jacobson Moore on Thursday.

472
00:19:06.210 --> 00:19:08.810
Well. don't kiss me in
public or you'll blow my cover.

473
00:19:08.920 --> 00:19:10.496
No. no. You should have

474
00:19:10.520 --> 00:19:13.126
heard me arguing with
Julian about the terms

475
00:19:13.150 --> 00:19:14.996
of the audit. I held my ground

476
00:19:15.020 --> 00:19:18.220
like coriolanus with a calculator.

477
00:19:18.360 --> 00:19:21.960
And Debra's bringing in
receipts going back to 2005.

478
00:19:23.800 --> 00:19:25.506
Wow. tough crowd.

479
00:19:25.530 --> 00:19:28.446
Joey called. and he wants
to talk to us in person.

480
00:19:28.470 --> 00:19:29.746
- no.
- And I said yes.

481
00:19:29.770 --> 00:19:31.816
- Madeline.
- We can't close the door on him.

482
00:19:31.840 --> 00:19:33.186
That's what we did with Ellie.

483
00:19:33.210 --> 00:19:35.380
and I've never stopped regretting it.

484
00:19:35.510 --> 00:19:37.856
Okay. if you want us
to hear him out. fine.

485
00:19:37.880 --> 00:19:40.286
but I am not gonna change my mind.

486
00:19:40.310 --> 00:19:42.526
I am not going back into the cycle

487
00:19:42.550 --> 00:19:44.990
and he's going to be lying anyway.

488
00:19:46.220 --> 00:19:47.826
I'll remind you. Mr. Hammond.

489
00:19:47.850 --> 00:19:49.920
depositions are under oath.

490
00:19:50.060 --> 00:19:52.736
So. is that you in this video?

491
00:19:52.760 --> 00:19:55.400
Yes. that's me.

492
00:19:56.200 --> 00:19:58.206
Why were you washing your car

493
00:19:58.230 --> 00:20:00.576
in a dark alley at 11:00 at night?

494
00:20:00.600 --> 00:20:02.546
I vomited.

495
00:20:02.570 --> 00:20:03.916
Food poisoning.

496
00:20:03.940 --> 00:20:06.940
I couldn't make it home. so I pulled over.

497
00:20:07.070 --> 00:20:09.056
Some of it got on the bumper.
so I found the nearest hose

498
00:20:09.080 --> 00:20:11.256
and rinsed it off. then

499
00:20:11.280 --> 00:20:13.156
I drove the rest of the way home.

500
00:20:13.180 --> 00:20:14.686
Can anyone corroborate your story?

501
00:20:14.710 --> 00:20:17.326
My ex-wife was asleep
when I got home. my daughter

502
00:20:17.350 --> 00:20:19.420
- was with her boyfriend.
- That's convenient.

503
00:20:19.550 --> 00:20:21.226
- Travis.
- If the plaintiff is gonna interject.

504
00:20:21.250 --> 00:20:23.250
- we should recess.
- We're good. There won't be

505
00:20:23.390 --> 00:20:24.836
any further interruptions.

506
00:20:24.860 --> 00:20:27.530
I do share my client's skepticism.

507
00:20:28.260 --> 00:20:30.406
You sure it wasn't alcohol poisoning?

508
00:20:30.430 --> 00:20:32.506
I was not drinking and driving that night.

509
00:20:32.530 --> 00:20:35.300
I mean. you do have several duis.

510
00:20:37.000 --> 00:20:38.846
That was a very shameful

511
00:20:38.870 --> 00:20:40.846
period of my life. but I've changed.

512
00:20:40.870 --> 00:20:42.270
I'm grateful for a second chance.

513
00:20:42.380 --> 00:20:44.356
You know who didn't get
a second chance? My dad.

514
00:20:44.380 --> 00:20:45.786
- He didn't get a second chance.
- We're done with this deposition.

515
00:20:45.810 --> 00:20:47.126
- Wait.
- Let's resume

516
00:20:47.150 --> 00:20:48.696
once you get a handle on your client.

517
00:20:48.720 --> 00:20:50.456
Go ahead. Hide behind your lawyer.

518
00:20:50.480 --> 00:20:52.156
You've been hiding
all these years because

519
