778
00:34:17.290 --> 00:34:19.166
I thought I had it handled. but I guess.

779
00:34:19.190 --> 00:34:21.606
the case brought everything back.

780
00:34:21.630 --> 00:34:23.176
Feel like I'm 17 again.

781
00:34:23.200 --> 00:34:25.506
yelling at my dad about my curfew.

782
00:34:25.530 --> 00:34:28.130
That's what we were arguing about.

783
00:34:28.900 --> 00:34:31.600
Over 30 stupid minutes.

784
00:34:32.570 --> 00:34:34.616
- If I hadn't walked out...
- You can't

785
00:34:34.640 --> 00:34:37.046
blame yourself. Travis.

786
00:34:37.070 --> 00:34:39.470
How do I stop?

787
00:34:43.480 --> 00:34:45.280
Cold Turkey.

788
00:34:46.050 --> 00:34:48.120
Just make the decision.

789
00:34:49.660 --> 00:34:51.596
And that works?

790
00:34:53.460 --> 00:34:55.266
I don't know. son.

791
00:34:55.290 --> 00:34:57.490
It's worth a try.

792
00:35:02.500 --> 00:35:05.646
What's. what's going on. buddy?

793
00:35:07.140 --> 00:35:10.616
Yeah... I was just eating yogurt.

794
00:35:10.640 --> 00:35:12.986
and then my heart
started beating really fast

795
00:35:13.010 --> 00:35:14.726
and then I was kind of hyperventilating.

796
00:35:14.750 --> 00:35:17.626
so I think I just... I think
I just had a panic attack.

797
00:35:17.650 --> 00:35:18.956
Or yogurt.

798
00:35:18.980 --> 00:35:21.020
'Cause you don't know
who you should work for.

799
00:35:21.850 --> 00:35:23.150
Exactly.

800
00:35:23.260 --> 00:35:24.636
Well. what's the rush? You'll figure it out.

801
00:35:24.660 --> 00:35:27.360
Yeah. but I... I don't like not knowing.

802
00:35:27.490 --> 00:35:28.736
I always know.

803
00:35:28.760 --> 00:35:30.436
In high school. I aimed for college.

804
00:35:30.460 --> 00:35:32.006
in college. I aimed for law school

805
00:35:32.030 --> 00:35:34.200
and then in law school. I
aimed for Jacobson Moore

806
00:35:34.330 --> 00:35:37.846
and then Olympia and...
And now you don't know.

807
00:35:37.870 --> 00:35:39.686
which is hard 'cause
you're addicted to goalposts

808
00:35:39.710 --> 00:35:42.050
and the hit you get when you clear one.

809
00:35:44.140 --> 00:35:45.516
So what should I do?

810
00:35:45.540 --> 00:35:46.770
Play dodgeball.

811
00:35:46.880 --> 00:35:48.256
Okay. I'd like to think you're joking.

812
00:35:48.280 --> 00:35:49.896
but that dopey grin tells me otherwise.

813
00:35:49.920 --> 00:35:51.526
You'll-you'll know when
you know. In the meantime.

814
00:35:51.550 --> 00:35:54.026
you... you got to get rid
of that nervous energy.

815
00:35:54.050 --> 00:35:56.666
And you're in luck. 'cause I have an in

816
00:35:56.690 --> 00:35:58.210
with the captain of my dodgeball team.

817
00:35:59.090 --> 00:36:00.336
I'm the captain.

818
00:36:00.360 --> 00:36:02.730
Okay.

819
00:36:04.660 --> 00:36:07.200
Arthur the accountant came through.

820
00:36:09.770 --> 00:36:11.716
Olympia and Julian are knee-deep

821
00:36:11.740 --> 00:36:17.016
in Debra's 2010 records
looking for the 350.000.

822
00:36:17.040 --> 00:36:18.910
I'm glad it worked.

823
00:36:20.180 --> 00:36:23.226
Have you come to your senses?

824
00:36:23.250 --> 00:36:24.580
About Joey?

825
00:36:25.420 --> 00:36:26.566
Yeah.

826
00:36:26.590 --> 00:36:29.090
I've heard you yell...

827
00:36:29.220 --> 00:36:32.560
A total of three times
in our entire marriage.

828
00:36:33.560 --> 00:36:39.006
Stubborn. strident. reactive. unforgiving?

829
00:36:39.030 --> 00:36:41.706
It... that's just not you.

830
00:36:41.730 --> 00:36:45.746
And I... I'm trying to figure out why.

831
00:36:45.770 --> 00:36:51.210
And I think... you have
some PTSD from Ellie.

832
00:36:52.380 --> 00:36:55.620
Madeline. I have processed my grief.

833
00:36:55.750 --> 00:36:57.026
Yes. your grief.

834
00:36:57.050 --> 00:37:00.720
But you haven't handled your trauma.

835
00:37:01.520 --> 00:37:03.366
The relapses.

836
00:37:03.390 --> 00:37:05.590
The constant panic.

837
00:37:06.690 --> 00:37:09.460
Loving someone that intensely

838
00:37:09.600 --> 00:37:13.246
and hating them and fearing for them.

839
00:37:13.270 --> 00:37:16.570
That's a deep trauma. Edwin.

840
00:37:17.370 --> 00:37:19.470
That's PTSD.

841
00:37:21.710 --> 00:37:24.310
It was when Joey disappeared.

842
00:37:26.550 --> 00:37:28.590
I went back...

843
00:37:29.980 --> 00:37:31.756
To Ellie.

844
00:37:31.780 --> 00:37:33.150
I know.

845
00:37:36.290 --> 00:37:38.460
But Joey is not Ellie.

846
00:37:39.590 --> 00:37:42.330
And Alfie is no longer a baby.

847
00:37:43.460 --> 00:37:44.660
And...

848
00:37:45.600 --> 00:37:47.500
I'm a different person. too.

849
00:37:51.600 --> 00:37:55.140
You held my hand when I
was looking into the abyss.

850
00:38:05.120 --> 00:38:07.860
I just want what's best for Alfie.

851
00:38:09.820 --> 00:38:11.660
I know.

852
00:38:21.870 --> 00:38:22.870
Tag!

853
00:38:23.000 --> 00:38:24.616
You're out. red 12.

854
00:38:24.640 --> 00:38:25.676
Same team.

855
00:38:25.700 --> 00:38:27.316
You're red 12. remember?

856
00:38:27.340 --> 00:38:29.710
I never knew how satisfying it would feel

857
00:38:29.840 --> 00:38:31.180
to throw balls at people.

858
00:38:31.310 --> 00:38:33.556
Did you see that one guy I
gave. like. two black eyes to?

859
00:38:33.580 --> 00:38:34.986
The referee? Yeah. You also set

860
00:38:35.010 --> 00:38:36.710
a new league record for yellow cards.

861
00:38:36.820 --> 00:38:40.150
Important thing is you
know your move. right?

862
00:38:42.950 --> 00:38:44.196
Yeah.

863
00:38:44.220 --> 00:38:48.906
So. I know you asked
me for an answer. and...

864
00:38:48.930 --> 00:38:51.070
My answer is that I don't know.

865
00:38:51.960 --> 00:38:56.206
And the merger is
closing in two weeks. so...

866
00:38:56.230 --> 00:38:59.400
I am going to take the
full two weeks to decide.

867
00:39:00.240 --> 00:39:03.016
And I hope that you can respect that.

868
00:39:03.040 --> 00:39:05.116
because I am worth the wait.

869
00:39:05.140 --> 00:39:07.240
I agree.

870
00:39:08.050 --> 00:39:09.520
I'll wait.

871
00:39:14.020 --> 00:39:16.560
I shouldn't have let things get
so out of hand the other night.

872
00:39:16.690 --> 00:39:20.490
I-I'm sorry for everything. I really am.

873
00:39:22.930 --> 00:39:24.536
Hey.

874
00:39:30.940 --> 00:39:33.180
I'm sorry. Alfie.

875
00:39:34.070 --> 00:39:36.770
For not sticking around
when I knew about you.

876
00:39:36.910 --> 00:39:39.080
For not being honest.

877
00:39:40.180 --> 00:39:43.756
But mostly. I'm sorry about
all the years I missed out on.

878
00:39:43.780 --> 00:39:46.680
I know what a great kid you are. Alfie.

879
00:39:46.790 --> 00:39:49.430
and my slipup had
nothing to do with you.

880
00:39:50.920 --> 00:39:52.590
But me being back here...

881
00:39:53.590 --> 00:39:55.390
Has everything to do with you.

882
00:40:07.370 --> 00:40:08.540
Come on.

883
00:40:18.280 --> 00:40:20.120
That sounds so sweet.

884
00:40:20.250 --> 00:40:22.296
It really was.

885
00:40:22.320 --> 00:40:24.966
A catbird moment. truly.

886
00:40:24.990 --> 00:40:26.636
I remember that.

887
00:40:26.660 --> 00:40:31.576
I was seven. and I wanted
to see a catbird so badly.

888
00:40:31.600 --> 00:40:33.036
You took me to that preserve.

889
00:40:33.060 --> 00:40:35.076
Yeah. and when you
saw that little grey bird.

890
00:40:35.100 --> 00:40:36.876
you burst into tears.

891
00:40:36.900 --> 00:40:38.816
Just... "It's just"

892
00:40:38.840 --> 00:40:41.286
"a boring bird. I thought it was gonna be

893
00:40:41.310 --> 00:40:43.116
- something special."
- No whiskers.

894
00:40:43.140 --> 00:40:46.486
- no fur. False advertising.
- And "catbird"

895
00:40:46.510 --> 00:40:50.150
became our code for something special.

896
00:40:51.650 --> 00:40:53.520
Which is why...

897
00:40:55.990 --> 00:40:58.190
You didn't.

898
00:40:58.960 --> 00:41:00.430
Well. what do you want now?

899
00:41:01.490 --> 00:41:02.690
A tattoo.

900
00:41:02.830 --> 00:41:04.700
I need something to hold on to.

901
00:41:08.570 --> 00:41:12.210
It's a way to keep you with me always.

902
00:41:13.770 --> 00:41:16.540
Because I have to let you go again.

903
00:41:17.810 --> 00:41:20.380
As painful as that might be.

904
00:41:21.450 --> 00:41:22.986
I love you. mom.

905
00:41:23.010 --> 00:41:25.210
I love you. Ellie.

906
00:41:38.360 --> 00:41:39.706
Any luck?

907
00:41:39.730 --> 00:41:42.476
It took a minute. but Matty.
we got what we needed.

908
00:41:42.500 --> 00:41:44.346
- What do you mean?
- There is a cash withdrawal

909
00:41:44.370 --> 00:41:47.910
for 350k. and it left her
account the day before

910
00:41:48.040 --> 00:41:49.710
the wolf visited priva.

911
00:41:49.840 --> 00:41:51.456
We got our proof.

912
00:41:51.480 --> 00:41:53.856
We've tied senior to the hush money.

913
00:41:57.050 --> 00:41:58.490
Is everything okay?

914
00:41:59.420 --> 00:42:00.626
Yeah.

915
00:42:00.650 --> 00:42:02.890
It's better than okay.

916
00:42:03.820 --> 00:42:05.420
Today feels like day one.

